{"title":"Formulas_Esenciales_UCI_iPad","guid":"","filepath":"/Users/criaah/Vault/📚 Resources/Mapas-Mentales/Entidades clínicas/UCI-Medicina Crítica/Formulas_Esenciales_UCI_iPad.smmx","root":{"id":"0","parent":"-1","text":"Fórmulas\\NEsenciales en UCI","guid":"fH6n4wcKtBhp0OnYZJKkWA","children":[{"id":"1","parent":"0","text":"Concepto General","guid":"LbtsQhF8HRU3N_gbfyEH4A","children":[{"id":"2","parent":"1","text":"PAM >65 mmHg → garantiza perfusión tisular","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"3","parent":"1","text":"Si aumenta presión intracompartimental → PAM no logra perfundir","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"4","parent":"1","text":"Presiones de perfusión = PAM - presión del compartimento","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"5","parent":"1","text":"Fórmula PAM = (2 x PAD + PAS) / 3","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"6","parent":"0","text":"1. Presión de Perfusión\\NCerebral (PPC)","guid":"EzastEt0AqQgcVnFBraAdQ","children":[{"id":"7","parent":"6","text":"Fórmula → PPC = PAM - PIC","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"8","parent":"6","text":"Meta → 60-80 mmHg (IDEAL ~70 mmHg)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"9","parent":"6","text":"PPC <50 mmHg → MUY MAL PRONÓSTICO","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"10","parent":"6","text":"PPC >80 mmHg → sin beneficio adicional","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"11","parent":"6","text":"Medición PIC","guid":"","children":[{"id":"12","parent":"11","text":"Catéter intraventricular → GOLD STANDARD","guid":"","children":[{"id":"13","parent":"12","text":"Dx + terapéutico (drenaje LCR)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"14","parent":"11","text":"Intraparenquimatoso → solo diagnóstico","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"15","parent":"11","text":"Subrogados si\\Nno hay catéter","guid":"RphnhlkhtJ4QoSyiIrs6VQ","children":[{"id":"16","parent":"15","text":"Diámetro vaina nervio óptico (ecografía)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"17","parent":"15","text":"Doppler transcraneal","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"18","parent":"6","text":"Doctrina Monro-Kellie","guid":"","children":[{"id":"19","parent":"18","text":"Bóveda craneal = baja distensibilidad","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"20","parent":"18","text":"3 componentes → tejido cerebral + LCR + sangre","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"21","parent":"18","text":"Aumento de cualquiera → aumento PIC","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"22","parent":"6","text":"Causas de aumento PIC","guid":"","children":[{"id":"23","parent":"22","text":"Clínicas → ECV isquémico, hemorragia, HSA, neuroinfección, encefalopatía hepática","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"24","parent":"22","text":"Traumáticas → hematoma epidural/subdural, HSA traumática, contusiones hemorrágicas","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"25","parent":"6","text":"Manejo (transitorio hasta\\Nresolución etiológica)","guid":"LUqm5VBa0KI87sTRBRPduQ","children":[{"id":"26","parent":"25","text":"Aumentar PAM con norepinefrina (transitorio)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"27","parent":"25","text":"Sedación profunda (BIS <25)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"28","parent":"25","text":"Bloqueo neuromuscular si amerita","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"29","parent":"25","text":"Soluciones hiperosmolares (hipertónico transitorio)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"30","parent":"25","text":"Drenaje LCR (si catéter intraventricular)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"31","parent":"25","text":"Craniectomía descompresiva → TEMPRANA (primeras horas)","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"32","parent":"0","text":"2. Presión de Perfusión\\NAbdominal (PPA)","guid":"B4tL_B2OECZEZ0LeKl7RMA","children":[{"id":"33","parent":"32","text":"Fórmula → PPA = PAM - PIA","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"34","parent":"32","text":"Meta → PPA ≥60 mmHg","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"35","parent":"32","text":"Hipertensión intraabdominal → PIA >12 mmHg","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"36","parent":"32","text":"Síndrome compartimental abdominal → PIA >20-22 mmHg sostenida","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"37","parent":"32","text":"Medición PIA","guid":"","children":[{"id":"38","parent":"37","text":"Sonda Foley 3 vías + transductor de presión → a monitor","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"39","parent":"37","text":"Método artesanal → columna plástica graduada (cm H2O)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"40","parent":"37","text":"Conversión → 1 mmHg = 1.36 cm H2O","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"41","parent":"32","text":"Causas de\\Naumento PIA","guid":"NPu050UKAVEXF3vhTat0gQ","children":[{"id":"42","parent":"41","text":"Clínicas → pancreatitis, isquemia/trombosis intestinal, sobrereanimación hídrica","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"43","parent":"41","text":"Traumáticas → trauma cerrado de abdomen, hemoperitoneo","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"44","parent":"32","text":"Manejo","guid":"","children":[{"id":"45","parent":"44","text":"Aumentar PAM transitoriamente (vasopresores)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"46","parent":"44","text":"Sondas rectales/gástricas → descompresión","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"47","parent":"44","text":"Diuréticos si sobrecarga hídrica","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"48","parent":"44","text":"Laparotomía descompresiva (incisión línea alba) → definitivo","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"49","parent":"0","text":"3. Driving Pressure (ΔP o\\NPresión de Distensión Alveolar)","guid":"ALCoAXG88INKLVsqfS9P5A","children":[{"id":"50","parent":"49","text":"Fórmula → ΔP = Presión Meseta - PEEP","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"51","parent":"49","text":"Meta → ΔP <15 cm H2O","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"52","parent":"49","text":"ΔP >15 cm H2O → AUMENTO DE MORTALIDAD","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"53","parent":"49","text":"Mide deformación (strain) alveolar ciclo a ciclo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"54","parent":"49","text":"Presión Meseta\\N(Plateau)","guid":"eMeknDP-RQJhwfQ9JoMQ3g","children":[{"id":"55","parent":"54","text":"Pausa inspiratoria ≥0.3-0.5 seg → medición confiable","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"56","parent":"54","text":"Refleja presión del PARÉNQUIMA pulmonar","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"57","parent":"54","text":"Flujo cero → elimina resistencia de vía aérea","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"58","parent":"49","text":"Causas de\\NΔP elevada","guid":"RXpiFxj57FglpBi-WLEOzA","children":[{"id":"59","parent":"58","text":"Baja compliance pulmonar → SDRA, edema pulmonar","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"60","parent":"58","text":"Volumen tidal excesivo → mala programación del ventilador","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"61","parent":"49","text":"Manejo de ΔP\\Nelevada","guid":"ZG3u_EYVcoNfZ49BKwZWgw","children":[{"id":"62","parent":"61","text":"Test de PEEP → si es respondedor, subir PEEP acorta ΔP","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"63","parent":"61","text":"Disminuir volumen tidal","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"64","parent":"61","text":"Prono","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"65","parent":"61","text":"Tabla PEEP/FiO2 (ARDSNet)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"66","parent":"61","text":"PRECAUCIÓN → Pplat <25-28 cm H2O al ajustar PEEP","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"67","parent":"49","text":"Evidencia","guid":"","children":[{"id":"68","parent":"67","text":"Costa et al. Am J Respir Crit\\NCare Med 2021;204(3):303-311","guid":"HzcnInAIu-RNwZDYTIHOBw","children":[{"id":"69","parent":"68","text":"ΔP predictor mortalidad con impacto 4x mayor que FR","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"70","parent":"68","text":"Modelo con ΔP + FR equivalente a mechanical power","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"71","parent":"68","text":"n=4,549 pacientes con SDRA","guid":"","children":[]}]}]}]},{"id":"72","parent":"0","text":"4. Variabilidad de\\NPresión de Pulso (VPP)","guid":"QGOMhgqwValRlavAR-7Ygg","children":[{"id":"73","parent":"72","text":"Fórmula → VPP = (PPmax - PPmin) / PPpromedio x 100","guid":"","children":[{"id":"74","parent":"73","text":"PPpromedio = (PPmax + PPmin) / 2","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"75","parent":"72","text":"VPP >14% → RESPONDEDOR a volumen (en contexto hipoperfusión)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"76","parent":"72","text":"VPP <10% → NO respondedor a volumen","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"77","parent":"72","text":"Concepto fisiológico","guid":"","children":[{"id":"78","parent":"77","text":"Interacción cardiopulmonar","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"79","parent":"77","text":"Ciclo respiratorio → cambios presión intratorácica → variabilidad arterial","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"80","parent":"77","text":"Arteria con bajo volumen → MÁS SENSIBLE a variabilidad respiratoria","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"81","parent":"77","text":"Arteria con volumen adecuado → POCA variabilidad","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"82","parent":"72","text":"Métodos de medición","guid":"","children":[{"id":"83","parent":"82","text":"Línea intraarterial → presión de pulso directa","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"84","parent":"82","text":"Pulsioxímetro de monitor hospitalario (NO de farmacia)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"85","parent":"82","text":"Variabilidad volumen sistólico (monitoreo mínimamente invasivo)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"86","parent":"82","text":"Doppler pulsado en carótida → variabilidad de flujo","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"87","parent":"72","text":"Limitaciones (condiciones\\Nde los ECA)","guid":"KD5lzxX87p5yTamyXToatg","children":[{"id":"88","parent":"87","text":"Ventilación mecánica CONTROLADA (no asistida)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"89","parent":"87","text":"Sin arritmias","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"90","parent":"87","text":"VT ≥8 mL/kg peso ideal/predicho","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"91","parent":"87","text":"Drive respiratorio alto → puede dar falso positivo sin hipovolemia","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"92","parent":"87","text":"Acidosis metabólica severa → puede alterar resultados","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"93","parent":"72","text":"Venas vs arterias","guid":"","children":[{"id":"94","parent":"93","text":"Venas = vasos de capacitancia → variabilidad por contenido Y continente","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"95","parent":"93","text":"Vasodilatación → variabilidad venosa sin necesariamente baja volemia","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"96","parent":"93","text":"Sistema arterial → más específico para evaluar volemia","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"97","parent":"0","text":"5. Extracción de\\NOxígeno (EO2)","guid":"Wwbv8AllJZQq5Y83W7eX8Q","children":[{"id":"98","parent":"97","text":"Fórmula → EO2 = SaO2 - SvcO2","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"99","parent":"97","text":"Subrogado simplificado del DO2/VO2","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"100","parent":"97","text":"Rangos de\\Ninterpretación","guid":"eyIWF3US6mFY5ufWc-m6sw","children":[{"id":"101","parent":"100","text":"EO2 20-30% → GASTO CARDÍACO NORMAL","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"102","parent":"100","text":"EO2 >30% → GC BAJO\\N(hipodinámico)","guid":"KREvYzqo3BMabMuSbouRew","children":[{"id":"103","parent":"102","text":"Sangre pasa LENTO → célula extrae MÁS O2","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"104","parent":"102","text":"Etiologías → choque hipovolémico, cardiogénico, obstructivo","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"105","parent":"100","text":"EO2 <20% → GC ALTO\\N(hiperdinámico)","guid":"U6LIa0AQ5FBHPKBHOBC3Zw","children":[{"id":"106","parent":"105","text":"Sangre pasa RÁPIDO → célula no alcanza a extraer O2","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"107","parent":"105","text":"Etiologías → choque distributivo (séptico, neurogénico, anafiláctico)","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"108","parent":"97","text":"SvcO2 → medición\\Ncorrecta","guid":"BiZW1CakL4hjFw3qJV199g","children":[{"id":"109","parent":"108","text":"Catéter venoso central bien posicionado","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"110","parent":"108","text":"Punta entre 4to-6to espacio intercostal","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"111","parent":"108","text":"EVITAR mezcla con sangre del seno venoso coronario (muy desoxigenada)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"112","parent":"97","text":"Integración\\Nhemodinámica","guid":"FqzrbDDYnsJx30v9VxB38w","children":[{"id":"113","parent":"112","text":"GC bajo = resistencias vasculares sistémicas ELEVADAS (compensación)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"114","parent":"112","text":"GC alto = resistencias vasculares sistémicas DISMINUIDAS (compensación)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"115","parent":"112","text":"Combinar con VPP → si EO2 alta + VPP alta → choque hipovolémico","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"116","parent":"0","text":"Perlas\\NClínicas","guid":"O4j0bEN0970e_1B1Y8daOw","children":[{"id":"117","parent":"116","text":"PAM >65 mmHg NO garantiza perfusión si hay hipertensión compartimental","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"118","parent":"116","text":"PPC ideal ~70 mmHg → <50 = mal pronóstico, >80 = sin beneficio","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"119","parent":"116","text":"Driving pressure es el MEJOR predictor individual de mortalidad en VM","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"120","parent":"116","text":"VPP es SOLO una pieza del rompecabezas → integrar con levantamiento pasivo de piernas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"121","parent":"116","text":"EO2 es un subrogado PRÁCTICO del estado hemodinámico si no hay monitoreo avanzado","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"122","parent":"116","text":"Aumentar PAM es TRANSITORIO → resolver causa del aumento de presión compartimental","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"123","parent":"116","text":"En presión meseta → pausa inspiratoria ≥0.3 seg para medición confiable","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"124","parent":"116","text":"Conversión → 1 mmHg = 1.36 cm H2O (útil en PIA artesanal)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"125","parent":"116","text":"Test de PEEP → no todo paciente con ΔP alta es respondedor a PEEP","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"126","parent":"0","text":"VER\\NTAMBIÉN","guid":"WXHmXBFM-ihBAXTyNHjWTA","children":[{"id":"127","parent":"126","text":"→ Fluidos en UCI (Reanimación)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"128","parent":"126","text":"→ Ventilación Mecánica SDRA (Ventilación)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"129","parent":"126","text":"→ Monitoreo Hemodinámico (Hemodinámica)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"130","parent":"126","text":"→ Choque Séptico (Hemodinámica)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"131","parent":"0","text":"Referencias","guid":"","children":[{"id":"132","parent":"131","text":"1. Costa ELV et al. Ventilatory Variables and Mechanical Power in Patients with ARDS. Am J Respir Crit Care Med. 2021;204(3):303-311.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"133","parent":"131","text":"2. Amato MBP et al. Driving pressure and survival in ARDS. N Engl J Med. 2015;372(8):747-55.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"134","parent":"131","text":"3. Michard F, Teboul JL. Predicting fluid responsiveness in ICU patients: a critical analysis. Chest. 2002;121(6):2000-8.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"135","parent":"131","text":"4. Malbrain MLNG et al. Principles of end-organ resuscitation and intra-abdominal hypertension. World J Emerg Surg. 2016;11:13.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"136","parent":"131","text":"5. Brain Trauma Foundation. Guidelines for the Management of Severe TBI. 4th Ed. Neurosurgery. 2017;80(1):6-15.","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},"node_count":136,"relations":[],"cross_references":[],"specialty":"UCI/Medicina Crítica","folder":"Entidades clínicas/UCI-Medicina Crítica","filename":"Formulas_Esenciales_UCI_iPad","id":"map_2323","resolved_references":[],"title_raw":"Formulas_Esenciales_UCI_iPad"}